<subSubSection id="C326E0F8A64A221038EB3A790F0A2D3D" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B83B373A64A221038EB3A790A982E11" blockId="15.[189,416,265,292]" box="[189,416,265,292]" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="B9486F61A64A221038EB3A790A0E2E16" bold="true" box="[189,310,265,291]" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(female)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83B373A64A221038EB3A480F0A2D3D" blockId="15.[188,1400,312,520]" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">
Body length 3.0– 
<quantity id="4CC41E96A64A221039DF3A480ADD2E66" box="[393,485,312,339]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
; antenna as long as body, F15 length 2.0 × its width (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64A22103C013A480F8E2E66" box="[1111,1206,312,339]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-190@14.[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Microplitis mandibularis Thomson, 1895, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0051. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Wings. E. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690344/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view, head width less than 2.0 × its length (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64A22103AD33A2C09DB2E42" box="[645,739,348,375]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-190@14.[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Microplitis mandibularis Thomson, 1895, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0051. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Wings. E. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690344/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
); anteromesoscutum and mesoscutellar disc coriaceous (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64A2210389E3AF10A1C2EAE" box="[200,292,385,411]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-190@14.[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Microplitis mandibularis Thomson, 1895, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0051. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Wings. E. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690344/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
); pterostigma length 2.5 × its width; vein R1 longer than pterostigma half; 1 
<superScript id="7C491E3BA64A22103CC83AF00F912EBB" attach="left" box="[1182,1193,384,398]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">st</superScript>
discal cell length 1.2–1.3 × its width; vein 1CUb 3.0 × as long as vein 1CUa (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64A22103BCA3AD508C52E8A" box="[924,1021,421,447]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-190@14.[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Microplitis mandibularis Thomson, 1895, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0051. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Wings. E. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690344/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
); T1 length 2.5 × its maximum width, T1 rugulose and parallel-sided (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64A22103AD53AB909E62ED6" box="[643,734,457,483]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-190@14.[198,1390,980,1925]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Microplitis mandibularis Thomson, 1895, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0051. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Wings. E. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690344" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690344/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
). Colour: body black; antenna and tegula reddish yellow; basal one third of pterostigma and legs yellow (except for black metacoxa).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
